race.comment: ALDEBARANSTILINSKI (14) has come from this same handicap to win in both rounds of this series so far, last time getting home by 6.7m. Unproven at this longer distance but has the form on the board. SASSY GALLEON (10) chased ALDEBARANSTILINSKI as runner-up two back then registered an effortless victory here last time out, scoring by close to 12m. Peaking at the right time so could turn the tables on the top pick. LOOK FOR TASCOTT (1) has come from this starting position to place behind Aldebaranstilinski in his last two outings. Can be competitive again. Wouldn't surprise to see SOUTHERN DIAMOND NZ (11) put it together in his first outing since arriving from NZ.
